    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-11-23T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-11-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <head>378. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d378fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 15-1 US/<persName
                            corresp="#p_KJF1">Kennedy</persName>. Limited Official Use;
                        Immediate.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Moscow</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-11-23T14:00:00+03:00">November 23, 1963, 2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1759. <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName>, accompanied by <persName
                        corresp="#p_GAA1">Gromyko</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SMN1"
                        >Smirnovsky</persName> (Head USA Section), Teplov (Acting Protocol Chief)
                    signed book of condolences at Spaso House 12:30 local time today.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d378fn1">For President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1"
                            >Kennedy</persName>, who was assassinated in Dallas, Texas, November
                        22.</note> I had previously been informed by <persName corresp="#p_SMN1"
                        >Smirnovsky</persName> who called personally at <gloss target="#t_EMB1"
                        >Emb</gloss>, that <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName> would
                    sign book and accordingly, I was on hand to meet him.</p>
                <p>In private conversation which followed signing ceremony, <persName
                        corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName> expressed his deep personal regret
                    and shock at death of President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1">Kennedy</persName>
                    for whom, he said, he had great admiration and respect; indicated he and his
                    family had sent messages of condolence to Mrs. <persName>Kennedy</persName>; and
                    advised that as measure respect and esteem, <persName corresp="#p_MAI1"
                        >Mikoyan</persName> would leave for US tomorrow to attend funeral as
                    official <gloss target="#t_SOV1">Sov</gloss> Govt representative. <persName
                        corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName> added that while he did not know
                    President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> personally, he felt
                    sure new President shared late Presidentʼs views and hoped he would have
                    opportunity meet and exchange views with him in future.</p>
                <p>I made appropriate reply to <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Khrushchev</persName>,
                    including expression of personal gratitude that he had chosen personally
                    register his esteem for late President by signing book of condolences.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SMN1">Smirnovsky</persName> indicated <persName
                        corresp="#p_MAI1">Mikoyan</persName>ʼs passport would be sent <gloss
                        target="#t_EMB1">Emb</gloss> today for visaing and presumably <gloss
                        target="#t_EMB1">Emb</gloss> will then learn and report <persName
                        corresp="#p_MAI1">Mikoyan</persName>ʼs precise travel plans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KFD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Kohler</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
